SCRIPT_MODULE\" script=\"null\" language=\"null\">Start module</module>\n    <module type=\"module\" id=\"8FFDC36C-5D7D-4DB4-8870-0264D704A71F\" key=\"0\" name=\"END\" img_src=\"images/closha/module/end.gif\" img_width=\"48\" img_height=\"48\" x=\"1290\" y=\"121\" parameter_number=\"0\" status=\"Complete\" isTerminate=\"0\" author=\"default\" version=\"1.0 \" app_format=\"SCRIPT_MODULE\" script=\"null\" language=\"null\">End module</module>\n    <module type=\"module\" id=\"9CA1F5DF-11FD-445C-B754-F71FDC1CF873\" key=\"2\" name=\"seqpig_sorting\" img_src=\"images/closha/module/module_1.gif\" img_width=\"48\" img_height=\"48\" x=\"191\" y=\"37\" parameter_number=\"2\" status=\"Complete\" isTerminate=\"0\" author=\"kogun82\" version=\"0.5\" app_format=\"SCRIPT_MODULE\" script=\"/home/hadoop/closha/script/kogun82/seqpig/seqpig_01_sorting.sh\" language=\"shell\">Sorting an input BAM file by chromosome, reference start coordinate, strand and readname (in this hierarchical order)</module>\n    <module type=\"module\" id=\"F26A8C49-C9FE-4089-A148-79B147610870\" key=\"3\" name=\"seqpig_basefreq\" img_src=\"images/closha/module/module_3.gif\" img_width=\"48\" img_height=\"48\" x=\"315\" y=\"146\" parameter_number=\"2\" status=\"Complete\" isTerminate=\"0\" author=\"kogun82\" version=\"0.5\" app_format=\"SCRIPT_MODULE\" script=\"/home/hadoop/closha/script/kogun82/seqpig/seqpig_02_basefreq.sh\" language=\"shell\">Computing base frequencies (counts) for each reference coordinate</module>\n    <module type=\"module\" id=\"3AC559BC-0590-48E2-A4B1-BA39F5C695F5\" key=\"4\" name=\"seqpig_pileup\" img_src=\"images/closha/module/module_4.gif\" img_width=\"48\" img_height=\"48\" x=\"390\" y=\"296\" parameter_number=\"2\" status=\"Complete\" isTerminate=\"0\" author=\"kogun82\" version=\"0.5\" app_format=\"SCRIPT_MODULE\" script=\"/home/hadoop/closha/script/kogun82/seqpig/seqpig_03_pileup.sh\" language=\"shell\">Generating samtools compatible pileup (for a correctly sorted BAM file with MD tags aligned to the same reference, should produce the same output as samtools mpileup -A -f ref.fasta -B input.bam)</module>\n    <module type=\"module\" id=\"AE59AF14-A460-42EC-9D26-6EA6A5497094\" key=\"5\" name=\"seqpig_read_stats\" img_src=\"images/closha/module/module_5.gif\" img_width=\"48\" img_height=\"48\" x=\"566\" y=\"295\" parameter_number=\"2\" status=\"Complete\" isTerminate=\"0\" author=\"kogun82\" version=\"0.5\" app_format=\"SCRIPT_MODULE\" script=\"/home/hadoop/closha/script/kogun82/seqpig/seqpig_04_read_stats.sh\" language=\"shell\">In order to evaluate the output of an aligner, it may be useful to consider the distribution of the mapping quality over the collection of reads. Thanks to Pig\'s GROUP operator this is fairly easy.</module>\n    <module type=\"module\" id=\"27C711E0-D0C5-4C61-B0EB-8F86C9C090E1\" key=\"6\" name=\"seqpig_basequal_stats\" img_src=\"images/closha/module/module_6.gif\" img_width=\"48\" img_height=\"48\" x=\"566\" y=\"44\" parameter_number=\"2\" status=\"Complete\" isTerminate=\"0\" author=\"kogun82\" version=\"0.5\" app_format=\"SCRIPT_MODULE\" script=\"/home/hadoop/closha/script/kogun82/seqpig/seqpig_05_basequal_stats.sh\" language=\"shell\">Sometimes it may be useful to analyze a given set of reads for a bias towards certain bases being called at certain positions inside the read. The following simple script generates for each reference base and each position inside a read the distribution of the number of read bases that were called.</module>\n    <module type=\"module\" id=\"7C783E29-7FD3-4D7D-9F41-9AF1ABD02DAE\" key=\"7\" name=\"seqpig_filter_mappability\" img_src=\"images/closha/module/module_11.gif\" img_width=\"48\" img_height=\"48\" x=\"958\" y=\"168\" parameter_number=\"3\" status=\"Complete\" isTerminate=\"0\" author=\"kogun82\" version=\"0.5\" app_format=\"SCRIPT_MODULE\" script=\"/home/hadoop/closha/script/kogun82/seqpig/seqpig_06_filter_mappability.sh\" language=\"shell\">The script filter_mappability.pig 